OL,6,FHis comments come as bin workers in
OL,7,FBirmingham voted on Monday to reject a
OL,8,F"totally inadequate" partial deal that
OL,9,Fcould have ended the ongoing strike.
OL,11,FThe ongoing strike has meant residents
OL,12,Fin some parts of Birmingham have not
OL,13,Fhad their bins collected for weeks.
OL,15,FUnite the Union is currently
OL,16,Fcampaigning against plans to cut a
OL,17,Fpost from Birmingham's refuse and
OL,18,Frecycling service, which it says will
OL,19,Flead to hundreds of its members having
OL,20,Ftheir pay cut by up to #8,000 a year.
